credit.credit-words: Music: Truman S. Wetmore (1774–1861) Text: Douglas Wilson, 2019

3. So as we hear His voice, We do not dare turn back In His great giving gracious joy We shall not ever lack.
4. God went with all of them And His Rock was the Christ, They drank the living water there, The life that has no price.
5. And so we drink in faith, We take the bread and wine We grow in Christian grace and peace As His great love designed.

6. His kindness offered us The holy wine and bread But with this holy meal of love Our gracious God has said,
7. “Do not resist My grace As in the wilderness, Do not give way to lust and sin And its deceitfulness.”
8. God’s love divine came down, God’s love the Table spread His offered bread is pure and white, His offered wine is red.
